{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "computelighting", "version": "2.0", "since": "14.5", "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute Lighting"], "extent": [81, 102]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Computes lighting using Physically Based Rendering."], "extent": [102, 162]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Also splits Shading Layers into the components required for surface shading. These are the surface color ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cf"]}, " (only need in non-PBR modes), the opacity ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Of"]}, " and the BSDF ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " (only need in PBR modes). This usually placed after any layer mixing with all the outputs plugged into an ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "VOP/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/VOP/output"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables and Parameters"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " node."], "extent": [162, 522]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When creating any VOP shader node, this node is automatically created and connected to the shader\u2019s layer output."], "extent": [522, 637]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Depending on the rendering engine being used, this node takes on slightly different roles. See the table below for technical details. Note that no action is required when switching between engines though, as long as all outputs are connected to a ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "VOP/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/VOP/output"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables and Parameters"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " Node."], "extent": [637, 958]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["In non-PBR modes"], "extent": [958, 976], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Compute lighting using the BSDF provided through the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " input or the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["layer"]}, " input\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " component. The result of this is the surface color output as ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cf"]}, ". The emission color ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Ce"]}, " is added to ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cf"]}, "."], "extent": [976, 1192]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["In PBR Modes"], "extent": [1192, 1206], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Because the PBR engine computes lighting itself based on a BSDF, this node doesn\u2019t do any computation and the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cf"]}, " output remains unused. The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " input or the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["layer"]}, " input\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " component are simply passed through to the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " output without modification."], "extent": [1206, 1476]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "ui", "text": ["Ce"]}, " is exported as a shader parameter and used as the emissive component by the PBR engine."], "extent": [1476, 1577]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1577, 1585], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["layer"], "extent": [1585, 1593], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When connected, the layer\u2019s components are used to compute lighting."], "extent": [1593, 1667]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1667, 1677], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["If any of the input\u2019s below are also connected, they override the layer component of the same name."], "extent": [1677, 1786]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["F"], "extent": [1786, 1789], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The BSDF used to compute lighting."], "extent": [1789, 1829]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["layer"]}, " is also connected, this input overrides the layer\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " component."], "extent": [1829, 1918]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Of"], "extent": [1918, 1922], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The opacity of the surface."], "extent": [1922, 1955]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["layer"]}, " is also connected, this input overrides the layer\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Of"]}, " component."], "extent": [1955, 2045]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Ce"], "extent": [2045, 2049], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The emission color of the surface."], "extent": [2049, 2089]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["layer"]}, " is also connected, this input overrides the layer\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Ce"]}, " component."], "extent": [2089, 2179]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2179, 2188], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Cf"], "extent": [2188, 2193], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The computed surface color. Plug this into an ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "VOP/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/VOP/output"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables and Parameters"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " Node\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cf"]}, " input."], "extent": [2193, 2331]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Of"], "extent": [2331, 2335], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The opacity. Plug this into an ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "VOP/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/VOP/output"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables and Parameters"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " Node\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Of"]}, " input."], "extent": [2335, 2459]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["F"], "extent": [2459, 2462], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The BSDF. Plug this into an ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "VOP/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/VOP/output"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables and Parameters"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " Node\u2019s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["F"]}, " input."], "extent": [2462, 2581]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Outputs"}], "title": ["Compute Lighting"], "summary": ["Computes lighting using Physically Based Rendering."]}